data.description: Active Under Contract - Accepting Back Up Offers The potential is endless and the canvas is blank - get ready to create your masterpiece! This super cute Spring Hill home is definitely a handyman's special, but it's a fantastic opportunity for investors or for anyone willing to put in the sweat equity. Located in a neighborhood with no HOA and minutes away from shopping and dining options, it's built on an extended 0.27 acre lot. Inside, the primary bedroom is a retreat with double closets and an ensuite bathroom featuring a walk-in shower. The two guest bedrooms are generously sized, offering ample closet space for storage. They share a guest bathroom with tub/shower combo. The heart of this home is the great room, perfectly situated just off the kitchen, which has plenty of counter and cabinet space. Glass sliding doors lead to a spacious lanai enclosed with vinyl windows, creating a delightful area for relaxation or entertainment. From the lanai, take in the view of the large backyard, fully fenced with chain link - ideal for landscaping enthusiasts or pet owners. Within 5 miles, you'll find Veterans Memorial Park, the Spring Hill Branch Library, the Hernando County YMCA, and even the local skating rink, Locomo. Explore the beauty of the nearby Adventure Coast; you can discover real mermaids at Weeki Wachee Springs State Park, along with a water park and canoe/kayak launch. Popular swimming destinations like Pine Island Park and Roger's Park are a short drive to the west, along with Linda Pedersen Park, Bayport Park, Jenkins Creek Park, and the Weeki Wachee Wildlife Management Area for nature enthusiasts. Centrally located between US-19 and the Suncoast Parkway, access to Homosassa, Tarpon Springs, Clearwater, and Tampa is nearby and convenient. The magic of Orlando and its theme parks is less than 2 hours to the east, too. If you're ready to unleash your creativity, the potential of this fixer-upper is endless. Seize the opportunity and schedule your showing today!
